<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2007-06-01</DATELINE><TITLE>High isolation rate of adenovirus serotype 7 from South Korean military recruits with mild acute respiratory disease</TITLE><BODY>Adenovirus is a major cause of acute respiratory disease (ARD) in military recruits. When South Korean military recruits with ARD were surveyed, adenovirus was identified in 122 (61.0%) of the 200 recruits studied. Moreover, all cases of ARD involving adenovirus were caused by serotype 7.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>